SIMPLE: silken
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Silken
<hw>Silk"en</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>seolcen</ets>, <ets>seolocen</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or
pertaining to silk; made of, or resembling, silk; <as>as,
<ex>silken</ex> cloth; a <ex>silken</ex> veil</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fig.: Soft; delicate; tender; smooth; <as>as,
<ex>silken</ex> language</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Silken</xex> terms
precise.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Dressed in silk.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A . . .
<xex>silken</xex> wanton.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Silken</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Silken
<hw>Silk"en</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To render silken or
silklike.</def> <rj><au>Dyer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Silkiness</ent>⟦br⟧
